The paper discusses stochastic gradient algorithms in the context of machine learning applications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The focus on matrix manifolds and the Grassmann manifold in particular suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of optimization algorithms and convergence rates suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The use of subspaces and constraints suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the use of logarithmic convergence rates suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
